    "With France's entry into World War II, he joined a tank division, was captured in 1940, but escaped.": [],
    "He spent three years, 1940-1944 with Josette, quietly writing, until he joined the French resistance.": [],
    "Arrested again by the Gestapo in 1944 in Toulouse, the city was shortly thereafter liberated and Malraux free again.": [],
    "He led the Alsace-Lorraine resistance brigade in 1945, adopting the sobriquet \"Colonel Berger.\"": [],
    "While engaged in the fighting in Alsace, Josette was killed in a railroad accident in southwest France the same year.</p>\n\n<p>The post-war government appointed Malraux Minister of Information in 1945 (which he held only for a year).": [],
